# 🛡️ Red Team Engagement Plan – Simulated Operation

## 🧠 Objective:
Simulate a realistic adversary attack targeting an internal corporate network to assess the organization’s detection, response, and mitigation capabilities.

> *This engagement is for educational and ethical practice only. Based on TryHackMe's "Red Team Engagement Plan" room.*

---

## 🔍 Scope of Engagement

| Item              | Details                          |
|-------------------|----------------------------------|
| Target Company    | `Acme Corp` (simulated)          |
| Environment       | Internal network (AD Lab)        |
| Timeframe         | 5 days                           |
| Team Members      | Red Team – Solo (Aniket Pal)     |
| Objective         | Domain Admin access + data exfil |
| Allowed Attacks   | Social Engineering, AD attacks   |
| Disallowed Attacks| Denial of Service (DoS), Ransom  |

---

## ⚙️ Rules of Engagement (RoE)

- 🛡️ **No permanent damage** to systems
- 👀 **Report** all vulnerabilities found
- 📁 **Store data securely**
- 🔒 Avoid triggering **blue team detection** (stealth approach)
- 📞 Daily communication updates with project lead (simulated)

---

## 🔗 Kill Chain Phase Overview (Based on MITRE ATT&CK)

| Phase              | Tools Used                     | Description |
|--------------------|--------------------------------|-------------|
| Reconnaissance     | Whois, Nmap                    | External discovery |
| Weaponization      | Custom payload + MSFVenom      | Payload creation |
| Delivery           | Phishing email (simulated)     | Entry vector |
| Exploitation       | EternalBlue, LPE (WinPrivEsc)  | Access via known exploit |
| C2 Setup           | Ngrok + Netcat, CobaltStrike   | Setup persistence and remote access |
| Post-Exploitation  | Mimikatz, BloodHound           | Lateral movement and creds dump |
| Exfiltration       | Rclone + Obfuscation           | Transfer sensitive files |
| Reporting          | Full markdown report created   | Includes timeline and artifacts |

---

## 📁 Deliverables

- [x] Initial Engagement Plan ✅
- [x] Attack Chain Summary ✅
- [x] Indicators of Compromise ✅
- [x] Tools + Tactics Used ✅
- [x] Recommendations ✅

